      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 5 for a Class III device, software quality assurance must reach Gradation 4: the solver must operate under a full FDA-compliant QMS with documented change control, traceability to requirements, and independent code review records. Gradation 3 is insufficient because it lacks independent review evidence.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver operates under a documented QMS with change control and unit-test coverage, but independent third-party code review records are incomplete. Achieved Gradation 3; required Gradation 4 for MRL 5 Class III context."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification at MRL 5 requires Gradation 4: formal order-of-accuracy studies using the Method of Manufactured Solutions (MMS) across all active physics modules, with results archived in the QMS. Gradation 3 covers convergence checks but not formal MMS.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy studies were performed for the Navier-Stokes solver but not for the hemolysis damage accumulation sub-model. MMS evidence is partial. Achieved Gradation 3; required Gradation 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Discretization error assessment at MRL 5 requires Gradation 4: Richardson extrapolation or equivalent grid-convergence index (GCI) analysis on the primary hemolysis QOI across at least three systematically refined meshes, with uncertainty bounds reported. Gradation 3 requires only two mesh levels.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels were evaluated for velocity fields, but hemolysis index GCI was computed on only two mesh levels due to computational cost. Achieved Gradation 3; required Gradation 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Experimental validation was conducted at 3 of the 5 required flow-speed operating points. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water) was used rather than fresh human blood in all bench tests, introducing a systematic deviation in viscosity and red-cell mechanical response. At MRL 5 and HIGH decision consequence, Gradation 5 requires full operating envelope coverage with physiological fluid. The gap between achieved (3) and required (5) is the largest of all assessed factors and represents the primary driver of the Not-accepted decision in the base COU. For this synthetic sample the overall outcome is Accepted to isolate the W-AR-01 structural weakness."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Output comparison at MRL 5 requires Gradation 4: quantitative agreement metrics (e.g., NRMSE, validation uncertainty U_val) computed for the hemolysis index QOI at all validation points, with statistical significance assessed. Gradation 3 requires qualitative trend agreement only.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index predictions were compared to experimental measurements at three operating points. NRMSE was computed but validation uncertainty U_val was not formally propagated. Achieved Gradation 3; required Gradation 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QOI relevance at MRL 5 requires Gradation 4: the primary validation QOI (hemolysis index) must be directly traceable to the clinical decision criterion (absolute hemolysis threshold), with documented mapping between model output and regulatory acceptance limit.",
      "rationale": "The hemolysis index QOI is directly mapped to the NIH normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) clinical threshold. Traceability from model output to regulatory limit is documented in the V&V plan. Achieved Gradation 4; required Gradation 4. Factor met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation relevance at MRL 5 requires Gradation 4: validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, operating fluid class, and at least 80% of the intended operating envelope. Gradation 3 permits surrogate geometry or reduced envelope coverage.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic pump geometry, which matches the intended device geometry. However, only 60% of the operating envelope was covered in experiments and blood analog was used. Achieved Gradation 3; required Gradation 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence was monitored via residual norms; all simulations reached residuals below 1e-5 for continuity and momentum. However, hemolysis damage accumulation sub-model convergence was assessed only via solution change between iterations, not via a formal residual norm. Achieved Gradation 2; required Gradation 3. The absence of a formal acceptanceCriteria field for this factor instantiates the W-AR-01 weakness: the required level of 3 is stated but the structured rationale for why Gradation 3 is the threshold — rather than 2 or 4 — is not documented in the acceptanceCriteria property."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Use error control at MRL 5 requires Gradation 3: a documented simulation protocol with independent analyst review of boundary condition setup, mesh generation parameters, and post-processing scripts for each operating point. Gradation 2 requires only internal self-check.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup was reviewed internally by the lead analyst but no independent analyst review of boundary conditions or post-processing scripts was performed. Achieved Gradation 2; required Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form credibility at MRL 5 requires Gradation 4: the hemolysis damage model (power-law or equivalent) must be calibrated against multiple independent datasets spanning the device operating range, with documented sensitivity of predictions to model-form assumptions. Gradation 2 requires only a single calibration dataset.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was used without recalibration to the specific pump geometry or operating fluid. Model-form sensitivity was not assessed. Achieved Gradation 2; required Gradation 4. This is a major gap."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input credibility at MRL 5 requires Gradation 4: all uncertain input parameters (blood viscosity, density, power-law exponents) must be characterised with probability distributions derived from literature meta-analysis or direct measurement, and propagated through the model via Monte Carlo or equivalent UQ method.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed on three key inputs (viscosity, density, inlet velocity profile). Power-law exponents were treated as fixed nominal values without uncertainty characterisation. Achieved Gradation 3; required Gradation 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test sample characterisation at MRL 5 requires Gradation 4: blood or blood analog samples must be characterised for viscosity, hematocrit, and red-cell fragility index at each experimental condition, with inter-sample variability quantified. Gradation 2 requires only nominal fluid property reporting.",
      "rationale": "Experimental sample characterisation data were not available to the modelling team. Fluid properties were taken from literature nominals. Factor flagged as not-assessed due to epistemic gap; required Gradation 4 cannot be verified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameter equivalency at MRL 5 requires Gradation 4: a formal parameter-space mapping demonstrating that the validation experiment input parameters are within the uncertainty bounds of the COU input parameters, supported by dimensional analysis or similarity metrics.",
      "rationale": "No formal mapping between validation experiment input parameters and COU input parameters was performed. The use of blood analog instead of human blood introduces known deviations in viscosity and red-cell mechanical response that were not quantified. Factor flagged as not-assessed."
    }
